This paper discusses the design and evaluation of routing algorithms for flying ad hoc networks (FANETs), which are wireless networks composed of small unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves the use of autonomous fixed-wing UAVs, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the challenges of maintaining communication links in a dynamic network topology, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the routing algorithms in terms of link performance and communication range, which could be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
